f(x)=0,x0 f(x)x1 f(x)=0f(x)!=0x2=x1-f(x1)/f(x1) x_{n+1}=xn-f(xn)/f(xn). f(x)=0

# cost function
nll <- function(X, y, beta) { 
  ##return negative log-likelihood
  beta = as.vector(beta)
  z <-  X %*% beta
  LL <- t(y) %*% z - sum(log(1 + exp(z)))
  return (-LL)
}
# 
hessian <- function(X, beta) {
  # returns the Hessian of the log-likelihood
  p<-logitWithBeta(X,beta)
  w <- diag(c(p * (1-p)))
  J <- t(X) %*% w %*% X
  return (J)
}
# 
gradient <- function(X, y, beta) {
  # returns the gradient of the log-likelihood
  p<-logitWithBeta(X,beta)
  score <- t(X) %*% (y - p)
  return (score)
}

# f(x)=0,x0
# f(x)x1 f(x)=0f'(x)!=0x2=x1-f(x1)/f'(x1)
# x_{n+1}=xn-f(xn)/f'(xn). f(x)=0
glm_Newton <- function(y, X, max.iter = 200, eps = 1e-10) {
  # using newton method
  n.beta <- ncol(X)
  B <-  matrix(NA,ncol = max.iter,nrow = n.beta)
  NLL <- rep(0,max.iter) ###negative LL
  B[,1] <- rep(0,ncol(X)) ##starting value
  NLL[1] <- nll(X,y,B[,1])
  for (i in 2:max.iter) {
    B[,i] <- B[,i-1]+solve(hessian(X,B[,i-1])) %*% gradient(X,y,B[,i-1])
    NLL[i] <- nll(X,y,B[,i-1])
    if (all(abs(B[,i]-B[,i-1]) < eps)) break;
  }
  B <- B[ , !apply(is.na(B), 2, all)] ##remove NA columns if there is any 
  NLL <- NLL[NLL>0] 
  return (list(B,NLL))
}

glm_GradientDescent <- function(y, X, max.iter = 200, eps = 1e-10) {
  # using gradient descent
  n.beta <- ncol(X)
  B <-  matrix(NA,ncol = max.iter,nrow = n.beta)
  NLL <- rep(0,max.iter) ###negative LL
  B[,1] <- rep(0,ncol(X)) ##starting value
  NLL[1] <- nll(X,y,B[,1])
  alpha <- 4/(svd(cbind(1, X))$d[1]^2)
  
  for (i in 2:max.iter) {
    B[,i] <- B[,i-1]+alpha*gradient(X,y,B[,i-1])
    NLL[i] <- nll(X,y,B[,i-1])
    if (all(abs(B[,i]-B[,i-1]) < eps)) break;
  }
  B <- B[ , !apply(is.na(B), 2, all)] ##remove NA columns if there is any 
  NLL <- NLL[NLL>0] 
  return (list(B,NLL))
  
}

glm_StochasticGradientDescent <- function(y, X, max.iter = 200, eps = 1e-10) {
  # using gradient descent
  n.beta <- ncol(X)
  B <-  matrix(NA,ncol = max.iter,nrow = n.beta)
  NLL <- rep(0,max.iter) ###negative LL
  B[,1] <- rep(0,ncol(X)) ##starting value
  NLL[1] <- nll(X,y,B[,1])
  alpha <- 4/(svd(cbind(1, X))$d[1]^2)
  
  for (i in 2:max.iter) {
    B[,i] <- B[,i-1]+alpha*gradient(X,y,B[,i-1])
    NLL[i] <- nll(X,y,B[,i-1])
    if (all(abs(B[,i]-B[,i-1]) < eps)) break;
  }
  B <- B[ , !apply(is.na(B), 2, all)] ##remove NA columns if there is any 
  NLL <- NLL[NLL>0] 
  return (list(B,NLL))
  
}
library(ggplot2)
library(rlist)
set.seed(5)
beta=matrix(c(0.5,1.2,-1),nrow=1,ncol=3)
  
logitWithBeta = function(X,beta){
  beta = as.vector(beta)
  return(1 / (1+ exp(-X%*%beta)))
} 

generateX<-function(N){
  X1=matrix(c(rnorm(N,0,1)),nrow=1,ncol=N,byrow=TRUE)
  X2=matrix(c(rnorm(N,0,1)),nrow=1,ncol=N,byrow=TRUE)
  X0=matrix(c(rnorm(N,1,0)),nrow=1,ncol=N,byrow=TRUE)
  return(matrix(c(X0,X1,X2),nrow=N,ncol=3))
}

simulation<-function(N=200){
  X=generateX(N)
  # dim(X) # 200,3

  # dim(beta) #1,3
  p =logitWithBeta(X,beta)
  Y= rbinom(N,1,p)
  # logisticLM=glm(Y~X,family=binomial(link='logit'))
  # summary(logisticLM)
  nr<-as.matrix(glm_Newton(Y,X,100,1e-10))
  beta_hat<-nr[[1]] # only save the final result
  return(beta_hat[,ncol(beta_hat)])
}

init_betahats<-function(R){return(data.frame(beta1=rep(0,R),beta2=rep(0,R),beta3=rep(0,R)))}
R=200
beta_hats200=init_betahats(R)
beta_hats500=init_betahats(R)
beta_hats800=init_betahats(R)
beta_hats1000=init_betahats(R)

putElementIntoBetahats<-function(beta_hats,betahat,index,R=200){
  if(is.null(beta_hats$beta1)){beta_hats$beta1<-rep(0,R);beta_hats$beta2<-rep(0,R);beta_hats$beta3<-rep(0,R)}
  beta_hats$beta1[index]<-betahat[1]
  beta_hats$beta2[index]=betahat[2]
  beta_hats$beta3[index]=betahat[3]
  return(beta_hats)
}
for (time in 1:R) {
a<-simulation(200);beta_hats200<-putElementIntoBetahats(beta_hats200,a,time,R)
b<-simulation(500);beta_hats500<-putElementIntoBetahats(beta_hats500,b,time,R)
c<-simulation(800);beta_hats800<-putElementIntoBetahats(beta_hats800,c,time,R)
d<-simulation(1000);beta_hats1000<-putElementIntoBetahats(beta_hats1000,d,time,R)
}

calc_mean<-function(){
 bh200=c(mean(beta_hats200$beta1),mean(beta_hats200$beta2),mean(beta_hats200$beta3)) 
 bh500=c(mean(beta_hats500$beta1),mean(beta_hats500$beta2),mean(beta_hats500$beta3)) 
 bh800=c(mean(beta_hats800$beta1),mean(beta_hats800$beta2),mean(beta_hats800$beta3)) 
 bh1000=c(mean(beta_hats1000$beta1),mean(beta_hats1000$beta2),mean(beta_hats1000$beta3)) 
 meanBH=data.frame(bh200,bh500,bh800,bh1000)
 return(meanBH)
}
meanBH<-calc_mean()
meanBH

 bh200=c(mean(beta_hats200$beta1)-beta[1],mean(beta_hats200$beta2)-beta[2],mean(beta_hats200$beta3)-beta[3]) 
 bh500=c(mean(beta_hats500$beta1)-beta[1],mean(beta_hats500$beta2)-beta[2],mean(beta_hats500$beta3)-beta[3]) 
 bh800=c(mean(beta_hats800$beta1)-beta[1],mean(beta_hats800$beta2)-beta[2],mean(beta_hats800$beta3)-beta[3]) 
 bh1000=c(mean(beta_hats1000$beta1)-beta[1],mean(beta_hats1000$beta2)-beta[2],mean(beta_hats1000$beta3)-beta[3]) 
 meanBHDev=data.frame(bh200,bh500,bh800,bh1000)
 return(meanBHDev)
}

from the results we can see that the effects of the optimization is becomeing better with the increase in sample size.
